On 4/23/03 5:04 PM, "Neorobb1(-at-)aol.com" <Neorobb1(-at-)aol.com> wrote:

> Here's the problem I found with the booster fan: It gets its power thru the
> ignition switch, shares its power with the coil, and thus is close to the
> point of overload whenever you switch it on.

I checked the wiring diagram and although the relay is triggered from the
ignition switch by grounding the other side via the heater lever, it's
powered (via 16A fuse) to the starter.

